---
description: Canonical spec files must be in-repo/on-branch for artifact placement
globs:
  - .agents/skills/drive-pr-local-review/SKILL.md
alwaysApply: false
---

When a workflow needs a “canonical spec” to decide **where to write artifacts**:

- Treat a canonical spec as a **file in this repo on the current branch**.
- If the only spec is **external/off-branch** (URL, other repo, or a file not present on the branch), treat it as an **expectation source**, but do **not** place artifacts “next to it”.
- In that case, choose an in-repo artifact directory (for example under `wip/`, if the workflow supports it).
